== Introduction

The REST API for the data historian is currently exposing the following enpoints:

* _{main-endpoint}_ :                                                                                   The main API of the historian which currently only contains endpoints for importing and exporting data.
  * POST <<import-csv,_{import-csv-endpoint}_>>:                                                        Un endpoint pour importer des points depuis des fichiers csv.
  * POST <<import-json,_{import-json-endpoint}_>>:                                                      An endpoint to import points sent in the body of the request, in json format .
  * POST <<export-csv,_{export-csv-endpoint}_>>:                                                        An endpoint to export points in csv format.
* GET <<grafana-hurence-datasource-root,_{grafana-hurence-endpoint}_>>:                                 The API to interact with Grafana using the hurence "Hurence-Historian" datasource plugin.
  * POST <<grafana-hurence-datasource-query,_{grafana-hurence-query-endpoint}_>>:                       Get the points of the historian.
  * POST <<grafana-hurence-datasource-search,_{grafana-hurence-search-endpoint}_>>:                     Get the name of the metrics stored in the historian.
  * POST <<grafana-hurence-datasource-search-tags,_{grafana-hurence-search-tags-endpoint}_>>:           Get the values for the specified key.
  * POST <<grafana-hurence-datasource-search-values,_{grafana-hurence-search-values-endpoint}_>>:       Get the annotations stored in the historian.
  * POST <<grafana-hurence-datasource-annotations,_{grafana-hurence-annotations-endpoint}_>>:           Get the keys available to use the endpoint '_/api/grafana/v0/tag-values_'.
* [DEPRECATED] GET <<grafana-simplejson-root,_{grafana-simplejson-endpoint}_>>:                         Get the possible values for the specified key.
  * POST <<grafana-simplejson-query,_{grafana-simplejson-query-endpoint}_>>:                            The API to interact with Grafana using the "SimpleJson" datasource plugin.
  * POST <<grafana-simplejson-search,_{grafana-simplejson-search-endpoint}_>>:                          Used to obtain historian points from a query.
  * POST <<grafana-simplejson-annotations,_{grafana-simplejson-annotations-endpoint}_>>:                Get names of historian metrics.
  * POST <<grafana-simplejson-tag-keys,_{grafana-simplejson-tag-keys-endpoint}_>>:                      Used to obtain the annotations stored in the historian.
  * POST <<grafana-simplejson-tag-values,_{grafana-simplejson-tag-values-endpoint}_>>:                  Get the keys available to use the endpoint '_/api/grafana/simplejson/tag-values_'.
     Get the possible values for the specified key.

The 'tag-keys' and 'tag-values' endpoints are only useful for Grafana.

